quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,60,"Recall when Moses said to his servant, \"I will not give up until I reach the junction of the two seas, even if I must press on for years"
  18,61,"But when they reached the junction where the two seas meet, they forgot their fish, which made its way into the sea and swam away"
  18,62,"So when they had moved on, [Moses] said to his servant, \"Bring us our lunch. We have certainly suffered hardship on this journey"
  18,63,"He [the servant] said, \"Remember when we rested by the rock? I forgot the fish there. And it was Satan who made me forget to pay attention to it. And amazingly, it found its way into the sea"
  18,64,"[Moses] said, \"That is what we were seeking.\" So they returned, following their own footprints"
  18,65,"There, they found one of Our servants, whom We had blessed with mercy from Us, and unto whom We had imparted knowledge of our Own"
  18,66,"Moses said to him, \"May I follow you, so that you will teach me some of the right guidance You have been taught"
  18,67,"He said, \"You will not be able to wait patiently with me"
  18,68,for how can you have patience for what you do not understand
  18,69,"[Moses] said, \"You will find me, God willing, patient, and I will not disobey you in [any] way"
  18,70,"He said, \"Then if you follow me, do not ask me about anything until I mention it to you"